{{multiple issues| {{Orphan|date=July 2018}} {{underlinked|date=July 2018}} }} {{Infobox officeholder |honorific-prefix = |name = Ralava Beboarimisa |image = Ralava Beboarimisa, ministre de l'Environnement, de l'Ecologie, de la Mer et des Forêts de Madagascar.jpg |imagesize = |smallimage = |alt = |caption = |order = |office = Minister of transport and meteorology of Madagascar |term_start = August 2017 |term_end = |order2 = |office2 = Ministry of Environment, Ecology, Sea and Forest |term_start2 = January 2015 |term_end2 = April 2016 |birth_date = 1978 |birth_place = Madagascar |death_date = |death_place = |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |birthname = |nationality = Malagasy |party = |otherparty = <!--For additional political affiliations--> |spouse = |partner = <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married--> |relations = |children = |residence = |alma_mater = [[Université Paris XII]] |occupation = |profession = Environmental Minister |cabinet = |committees = |portfolio = |signature = |signature_alt = |website = |footnotes = }} '''Ralava Beboarimisa''' (born 1978) is a [[Madagascar|Malagasy]] politician who is Minister of transport and meteorology of Madagascar and is best known for being Ministry of Environment, Ecology, Sea and Forest from January 2015 to April 2016.
One of the biggest problems Beboarimisa faced during his tenure as minister of the environment was the rapid deforestation and threat to the flora and fauna of the island that Madagascar is undergoing.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ralava Beboarimisa, le nouveau ministre de l'environnement a du pain sur la planche (Ralava Beboarimisa, the new Minister of the Environment has a lot to do)|url=https://www.madonline.com/ralava-beboarimisa-le-nouveau-ministre-de-lenvironnement-a-du-pain-sur-la-planche/|publisher=MadOnline|date=9 February 2015|accessdate=27 March 2018|language=French}}</ref> The first law he helped pass was the so-called "Beboarimisa law" which toughened the sanctions of cutting down redwoods in Madagascar.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ralava Beboarimisa : La nouvelle loi mettra fin aux trafics illicites et conduira au développement (Ralava Beboarimisa, the new Minister of the Environment has a lot to do)|url=http://www.midi-madagasikara.mg/economie/2016/01/25/ralava-beboarimisa-la-nouvelle-loi-mettra-fin-aux-trafics-illicites-et-conduira-au-developpement/|publisher=Midi-Madagasikara|date=25 January 2015|accessdate=28 March 2018|language=French}}</ref> Beboarimisa's hard tactics at combating deforestation made him a popular figure in the country, and for a brief period of time it was rumored that he might succeed [[Jean Ravelonarivo]] as the next prime minister.<ref>{{cite web|title=Primature Ralava Beboarimisa poussé dans la course (Primature Ralava Beboarimisa pushed into the race)|url=http://www.laverite.mg/politique/item/142-primature-ralava-beboarimisa-poussé-dans-la-course.html|publisher=La Vérité|date=10 March 2016|accessdate=27 March 2018|language=French}}</ref> However Beboarimisa ended up losing his job in April 2016 after more than 1,000 tons of redwood were discovered in possession of a Hong Kong businessman in Singapore, leading to questions how such a large amount could have been smuggled out of the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Madagascar - Singapore rosewood. Why Ralava Beboarimisa was dismissed|url=http://www.madagate.org/politique-madagascar/dossier/5706-madagascar-singapore-rosewood-why-ralava-beboarimisa-was-dismissed.html|publisher=MADAGATE|date=23 April 2016|accessdate=28 March 2018}}</ref>
